---
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../config/site';
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
  title={`${SITE_TITLE} AI Disclaimer`}
  description="How bangs.to relates to AI: site copy, local-first redirects, and why you should verify bang URLs and search providers yourself."
  currentPath="/ai"
>
  <div class="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(300px,0.72fr)_minmax(0,1fr)]">
    <aside class="card h-fit p-5 sm:p-6">
      <p class="text-xs font-700 uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-primary-700">AI disclaimer</p>
      <h1
        class="mt-2 max-w-[12ch] font-display text-[2.4rem] font-800 leading-[0.95] tracking-[-0.05em] text-text sm:text-[2.9rem]"
      >
        AI Disclaimer
      </h1>
      <div class="mt-5 grid gap-3">
        <div class="rounded-[22px] bg-bg-soft p-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-700 text-text">What we are</p>
          <p class="mt-3 max-w-[68ch] text-sm leading-7 text-text-secondary">
            bangs.to is a privacy-oriented, local-first !bang redirect: it routes what you type to
            search engines and sites using templates in your browser. All results are from other services. We do
            not provide answers to questions, interpret intent beyond bang expansion, or replace the destination
            site. Anything you read here is informational—verify important details yourself.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-[22px] bg-bg-soft p-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-700 text-text">Human intent, automated output</p>
          <p class="mt-3 max-w-[68ch] text-sm leading-7 text-text-secondary">
            Some site copy may be drafted or refined with AI tools; that output can be wrong while
            sounding plausible.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-[22px] bg-bg-soft p-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-700 text-text">Bang data and third-party sites</p>
          <p class="mt-3 max-w-[68ch] text-sm leading-7 text-text-secondary">
            Redirect URLs come from merged bang definitions and upstream catalogs; destinations are
            third-party services with their own behavior and terms. We do not guarantee the validity of the redirects, and you should verify the final URL and the provider's own documentation or support.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </aside>

    <div class="grid gap-4">


      <section class="card p-5 sm:p-6">
        <h2 class="section-title">Human intent, automated output</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 grid gap-3">
          <p class="max-w-[68ch] text-sm leading-7 text-text-secondary">
            Some pages or strings on bangs.to may be generated or refined with AI-assisted editing
            (for example drafting or tightening copy). Like any automated help, that can introduce
            mistakes, omissions, or wording that sounds authoritative but is not.
          </p>
          <p class="max-w-[68ch] text-sm leading-7 text-text-secondary">
            For how the product works, prefer the FAQ, instructions, and repository or deployment
            docs you trust. For search results and site behavior after a redirect, rely on the
            provider or site you opened—not this disclaimer page.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="card p-5 sm:p-6">
        <h2 class="section-title">Bang data and third-party sites</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 grid gap-3">
          <p class="max-w-[68ch] text-sm leading-7 text-text-secondary">
            bangs.to builds redirect URLs from merged bang data (see project codegen). Triggers,
            templates, and upstream catalogs can change over time; a bang that worked yesterday may
            differ today. The app does not guarantee that every destination remains valid, complete,
            or aligned with your expectations.
          </p>
          <p class="max-w-[68ch] text-sm leading-7 text-text-secondary">
            After you follow a redirect, you are interacting with third-party search engines and
            sites. Their privacy policies, results, paywalls, and rate limits apply—not bangs.to’s
            local-first redirect layer. If something looks wrong, check the final URL and the
            provider’s own documentation or support.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="card overflow-hidden p-5 sm:p-6">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-end justify-between gap-3">
          <h2 class="section-title">Tools</h2>
        </div>

        <div
